And whatsoever ye shall ask in my name, that will I do, that the Father may be glorified in the Son.  {ExV 40.10} 
     If ye shall ask any thing in my name, I will do it.  {ExV 40.11} 
     If ye love me, keep my commandments. Chap. 14:13-15.  {ExV 40.12} 
     If ye abide in me, and my words abide in you, ye shall ask what ye will, and it shall be done unto you.  {ExV 40.13} 
     Herein is my Father glorified, that ye bear much fruit; so shall ye be my disciples. Chap. 15:7, 8.  {ExV 40.14} 
     And there was in their synagogue a man with an unclean spirit; and he cried out,  {ExV 40.15} 
     Saying, Let us alone; what have we to do with thee, thou Jesus of Nazareth? art thou come to destroy us? I know thee who thou art, the Holy One of God.  {ExV 40.16} 
     And Jesus rebuked him, saying, Hold thy peace, and come out of him. Mark 1:23-25.  {ExV 40.17} 
     For I am persuaded, that neither death, nor life, nor angels, 
